- 2.0.2 | Mar 08 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] Connection tracking limit (CT_LIMIT): global per-IP connection limit via
      periodic conntrack table scanning; configurable threshold, scan interval,
      block duration, port/state filters, TIME_WAIT exclusion, CIDR exemptions;
      VNET per-IP overrides; temp-deny blocking with PERMBLOCK escalation;
      CLI: --ct-scan (manual scan), --ct-status (show config and active blocks)
[New] GeoIP country blocking: ipset-based high-performance country filtering
      using cc_deny.rules/cc_allow.rules with ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 codes and
      continent shorthand (@EU, @AS, @NA, @SA, @AF, @OC); tiered data sources
      (ipverse.net, ipdeny.com) with local caching; atomic ipset swap for zero
      downtime updates; audit mode (CC_LOG_ONLY) for impact measurement;
      dual-stack IPv4/IPv6 support; advanced syntax for per-port/protocol rules
[New] Granular CC advanced trust entry removal: apf -u of a specific advanced
      CC entry (e.g., tcp:in:d=22:s=ZZ) now removes only that entry and its
      iptables rules; bare CC entries, other advanced entries, and ipsets for
      the same country are preserved; ipset/cache cleanup occurs only when the
      last entry for a CC is removed; nuke-all behaviour for bare CC codes and
      continent shorthand (@EU) is unchanged
[New] --cc IP: GeoIP reverse lookup — look up which country and continent
      an IP address or CIDR belongs to using cached GeoIP data; portable
      awk CIDR containment with on-demand world data download
[New] CC_CACHE_TTL: per-file cache freshness for GeoIP data (default 24h);
      skips re-downloading unchanged country data on firewall start, reducing
      full load time from ~30s to ~0s when cache is fresh; set 0 for previous
      always-download behavior; distinct from CC_INTERVAL (days, --cc-update)
[New] Structured event logging via elog_lib.sh: dual log model (application log
      + JSONL audit trail at /var/log/apf/audit.log), output module registry,
      severity filtering; eout() backward-compatible as elog_lib wrapper;
      audit events for config_loaded, service_state, and rule_loaded lifecycle
[New] SYN flood protection: SYNFLOOD chain rate-limits inbound TCP SYN packets
      via iptables limit module; configurable rate/burst thresholds, LOG +
      DROP for excess, dual-stack support
[New] SMTP outbound blocking: SMTP_BLOCK restricts outbound SMTP (ports 25,
      465, 587) to whitelisted users/groups; SMTP_ALLOWUSER/SMTP_ALLOWGROUP
      exemptions; works independently of EGF toggle
[New] Temporary allow/deny with per-entry TTL: apf -ta/-td HOST TTL adds
      time-limited trust entries (300, 5m, 1h, 7d); automatic cron expiry;
      list with --templ, flush with --tempf; block escalation auto-promotes
      repeat temp denies to permanent via PERMBLOCK_COUNT/PERMBLOCK_INTERVAL
[New] Custom hook scripts: hook_pre.sh/hook_post.sh sourced before/after
      iptables rules; activated by chmod 750; preserved across upgrades
[New] Silent IP blocking: silent_ips.rules drops all traffic to/from listed
      addresses with no logging; IPv4/IPv6 supported; preserved across upgrades
[New] New CLI commands: -g PATTERN (search rules/ipsets/trust files),
      --rules (dump active rules for piping), --info (firewall status),
      --lookup HOST (trust file search), --validate/--check (config dry-run),
      --list-allow/--list-deny (filtered trust display),
      --cc/--cc-update (GeoIP status and refresh), --dump-config, -h/--help
[New] Per-port connection limiting via xt_connlimit: IG_TCP_CLIMIT and
      IG_UDP_CLIMIT with port:limit pairs, port range support, VNET binding
[New] ipset 7-field format: per-list refresh interval and max entry count;
      backward-compatible auto-migration from 4-field and 5-field formats
[New] Advanced trust syntax in CLI: apf -a/-d/-ta/-td/-u accept
      proto:flow:port:ip format (e.g., "tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8") for
      protocol/direction/port-scoped trust rules; duplicate detection, IPv6
      bracket syntax, and port ranges supported
[New] FQDN pre-resolution in trust system: hostnames resolved via getent
      before loading into iptables; multiple A/AAAA records, IPv6 support,
      configurable timeout via FQDN_TIMEOUT; resolved= metadata enables
      removal without DNS; refresh (apf -e) re-resolves FQDNs
[New] validate_config(): startup config validation with clear error messages
      covering interfaces, stop targets, rate/burst formats, connlimit
      syntax, RAB parameters, logging, expiry, and sysctl settings
[New] Ban expiry: structured addedtime=EPOCH markers in permanent trust
      entries for reliable expiry; backward-compatible with pre-2.0.2 entries
[New] Auto-detection for USE_IPSET, IPT_LOCK_SUPPORT, and DOCKER_COMPAT:
      each resolves at startup based on system capabilities; CentOS 6
      (iptables 1.4.7, no -w) safely degrades; replaces hardcoded defaults
      with "auto" (upgrade-safe via .ca.def)
[New] install.sh improvements: auto-detect default network interface on
      fresh install; auto-detect and disable conflicting firewall services
      (firewalld, ufw); post-install dependency warnings; CentOS 6 safe
[New] pkg_lib.sh v1.0.2 integrated: shared packaging library for backup,
      service lifecycle, cron, man page, and OS detection; RPM/DEB packaging
      infrastructure via pkg.manifest and pkg_gen.sh
[New] Unified download helper: curl primary with wget fallback, redirect
      following, timeouts, retries; all download sites migrated
[New] uninstall.sh: removes all system-wide artifacts including cron, man
      page, symlinks, and audit log directory; prompts before removing
      install directory and logs
[New] Bash tab completion: apf.bash-completion installed to
      /etc/bash_completion.d/apf; context-sensitive completions for trust
      hosts, temp TTL values, and country codes

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] install.sh: fix directory permissions (dirs=750, files=640); verify
      source files before install; remove unsafe pre-install rm -rf; prevent
      backup collision on rapid re-installs; replace hardcoded /sbin/chkconfig
      with command -v discovery; add root privilege check
[Fix] importconf: guard vnet/*.rules glob; fix INSTALL_PATH default; preserve
      custom files and hook permissions during upgrade; fix upgrade detection;
      fix dead-code EG_DROP_CMD migration with pkg_config_get/pkg_config_set;
      migrate DOCKER_COMPAT, USE_IPSET, IPT_LOCK_SUPPORT from "0" to "auto"
      on upgrade so upgraders get runtime auto-detection defaults
[Fix] importconf: gate auto-detect migration on source version < 2.0.2;
      sync top-level copy from files/extras/importconf; preserve TCR_PORTS
      on upgrade from pre-2.0.2
[Fix] Anchor grep/sed patterns across trust, expiry, and block escalation
      functions to prevent IP substring collisions
[Fix] cli_trust_remove(): spec-based iptables rule deletion with removal
      tracking; anchored comment cleanup; reject empty argument
[Fix] trust_parse_fields(): add set -f/set +f to prevent glob expansion
      on unquoted field split; valid_trust_entry() rejects *, ?, [ chars;
      strip control characters from trust comment field
[Fix] Add mutex_lock to -a, -d, -u, -ta, -td CLI handlers; closes race
      window with cron --temp-expire on flock-absent systems
[Fix] Advanced trust removal: also delete iptables rules from TGALLOW/TGDENY
      chains; entries from global trust files were left in live iptables until
      next refresh or restart
[Fix] flush_temp_entries(): move orphan comment cleanup after cli_trust_remove
      so FQDN resolved= metadata is available for IP resolution during removal
[Fix] trust validation: add hint for abbreviated CIDR notation (e.g., '0/0'
      -> '0.0.0.0/0') across cli_trust(), cli_trust_remove(), cli_trust_temp()
[Fix] lgate_mac(): use $VF_LGATE instead of undefined $LGATE_MAC; gateway
      MAC filtering was non-functional
[Fix] expirebans(): fix $ip variable shadowing global iproute2 path; defer
      removals until after iteration to avoid modifying trust files while
      reading; add date parse error handling
[Fix] Fast load: atomic snapshot writes via mktemp+mv; validate snapshots
      before iptables-restore; flush partial rules on restore failure; check
      firewall exit code to prevent saving broken state; backend marker
      tracking for nft/legacy compatibility
[Fix] cl_cports(): reset EG_DROP_CMD, SMTP, and connlimit variables between
      VNET iterations to prevent rule leaking
[Fix] sysctl.rules: fix wrong proc paths for secure_redirects,
      send_redirects, and proxy_arp; per-interface sysctls were silently
      never applied
[Fix] SMTP_BLK: add chain-exists guard for VNET re-sourcing; add to Docker
      compat flush chain list; warn on empty SMTP_PORTS
[Fix] refresh(): populate REFRESH_TEMP from trust files instead of
      iptables-save parsing; protect bare IPv6 entries during refresh;
      exit 0 when trust rules unchanged
[Fix] Cron lifecycle: clean runtime-created refresh.apf and apf_develmode
      entries during install, uninstall, and firewall stop; remove trailing &
      from cron_refresh() entry that prevented exit code tracking and allowed
      overlapping executions
[Fix] apf: restart (-r) now propagates exit codes from flush/start
      sub-invocations; prevents silent firewall-down with success exit code
[Fix] GeoIP --cc IP: fix IPv4-as-FQDN false positive; replace broken 3-octet
      prefix fallback with portable awk CIDR containment; on-demand world data
      download resolves any IPv4 to country; --cc CC auto-fetches missing cache
[Fix] GeoIP: IFS=',' leak from callers broke LOG rule LEXT word splitting in
      _geoip_add_simple_rules() and _geoip_add_advanced_rule(); defensive
      IFS reset at function entry prevents silent LOG rule corruption
[Fix] GeoIP --cc-update: always mark data timestamp on cached update; restore
      staleness warning age precision; prevents permanently stale "Last update"
      and repeated staleness gate triggers on cache-only runs
[Fix] GeoIP --cc: split "Active country blocks" into labeled subsections for
      denied and allowed countries; fix advanced entry regex to match =
      separator in detail view
[Fix] GeoIP temp CC expiry: expire_temp_entries() and flush_temp_entries() no
      longer destroy permanent CC entries when expiring temporary ones; new
      _expire_cc_temp_entry() removes only temp metadata and conditionally
      cleans up iptables/ipsets only when no permanent entry remains
[Fix] GeoIP CC removal: harden eval in LOG rule removal with format
      validation and IPv6 regex scope; match LOG rules by proto and port
      flags separately (iptables -S inserts -m tcp between -p tcp and
      --dport N); only process rules matching APF CC chain naming convention
[Fix] ipset_migrate_rules(): add 5-field (v2.0.1) to 7-field migration;
      5-field entries were silently dropped on upgrade
[Fix] glob_allow/deny_download(): validate entries with valid_host() instead
      of raw file copy
[Fix] ctlimit.apf: add valid_ip_cidr() guard on conntrack-sourced IPs;
      fix grep -Fv substring match that could remove unrelated IP entries;
      add numeric validation for VNET-overridden CT_LIMIT values
[Fix] CLI feedback: unknown options exit 1; error messages to stderr;
      trust_lookup() negative result to stdout; list() uses cat for pipes
      and silent pager fallback for TTY; checks $EDITOR before hardcoded list
[Fix] ovars(): filter shell conditionals from variable name extraction;
      internals.conf if/elif lines produced invalid variable name errors on
      stderr during apf -o and fast load startup
[Fix] Preserve file inodes: logrotate copytruncate for tail -f consumers;
      trim() uses cat+rm instead of mv; trim() excludes blank lines from
      data line count
[Fix] vnetgen: strip Docker @ifN suffix from ip link output to prevent
      duplicate VNET rules in containers
[Fix] Portability: replace bare rm/mv/cp with command rm/mv/cp across all
      shipping files for portable coreutils resolution on pre-usr-merge
      (CentOS 6, Ubuntu 12.04) and modern distros
[Fix] Code hygiene: variable quoting, CentOS 6 compatibility, mktemp for
      all temp files with signal-safe cleanup

  -- Changes --

[Change] Conntrack module migration: use -m conntrack --ctstate when available,
         falling back to -m state --state on legacy systems
[Change] trust_hosts(): single-pass loop replacing four-pass grep cascade;
      advanced syntax delegated to trust_entry_rule(); batch all rules via
      iptables-restore --noflush reducing lock acquisitions from O(n) to O(1)
[Change] File-based flock mutex: replace FD-based exec/flock with noclobber +
      PID fallback; EXIT trap releases lock on signal; trust CLI operations
      acquire lock for cron race prevention
[Change] ESTABLISHED,RELATED state tracking moved earlier in INPUT chain;
      established connections fast-path past VNET and port filtering
[Change] Fast load uptime threshold raised from 5 to 10 minutes
[Change] Consolidate 3 cron files into single cron.d.apf with daily restart,
      hourly ipset refresh, and per-minute temp expiry
[Change] ipset batch loading via ipset restore; reduces load time from
      minutes to seconds for large block lists
[Change] Performance: replace subprocess chains with bash builtins across
      hot paths; VNET parsing with builtins and glob patterns
[Change] help(): show readable option names; add new commands; hide aliases
[Change] Runtime file permissions: align chmod 600 to 640 for trust files
      and log files; matches install.sh convention
[Change] install.sh/uninstall.sh refactored to use pkg_lib primitives;
      sed path replacement optimized with grep -rl pre-filter
[Change] Remove dead bandmin() integration (cPanel, discontinued ~2014);
      eliminates bash SIGSEGV on GHA runners with newer kernels
[Change] Delete .ca.def (803 lines): rewrite importconf to use
      pkg_config_merge() from pkg_lib; AWK-based key=value merge replaces
      shell-eval heredoc template; preserves trust files, hooks, rules,
      permissions, and DLIST_*_URL customizations across upgrades
[Change] download_url(): log TLS diagnostic hint on download failure; log
      WARNING when TLS verification fails and insecure fallback succeeds;
      aids legacy system troubleshooting
[Change] --cc CC: show country detail (continent, rules status, cached data,
      live ipset stats) even when country code filtering is inactive;
      previously returned "inactive" with no information
[Change] GeoIP ipset operations use ipset list -t (headers only) instead of
      full member listing; eliminates O(n) scans on large ipsets
[Change] Integrate geoip_lib.sh v1.0.1: shared GeoIP metadata library
      replaces embedded country name table, continent lists, CC validation,
      download functions, and CIDR search; ~300 lines removed
[Change] GeoIP progress output: continent expansion and multi-CC downloads
      now show per-CC progress (e.g., "processing US (3/51)") via eout;
      eliminates silent 3-minute waits during @EU and similar operations
[Change] refresh(): exit 0 (not 1) when trust rules are unchanged since
      last refresh; semantically correct (unchanged is not an error) but
      may affect automation that checks for non-zero exit on no-op refresh
[Change] Decompose functions.apf (3,291 lines) into 8 sub-libraries via
      apf.lib.sh hub; absorb firewall as firewall_full_load() in apf_core.sh;
      rename geoip.apf/ctlimit.apf to apf_geoip.sh/apf_ctlimit.sh; upgrade
      cleans orphaned pre-decomposition files
[Change] Remove dead code: unused variables, unreachable branches, and
      deprecated function parameters across internal libraries
[Change] Update vendored pkg_lib.sh to v1.0.5: config merge API, sed escaping
      fixes, portable coreutils, temp-file safety
[Change] Update vendored elog_lib.sh to v1.0.4: JSON-escape fixes for RFC
      8259 compliance, fork reduction, hostname caching, shared helper
      extraction
[Change] Update vendored geoip_lib.sh to v1.0.4: convention compliance,
      input validation hardening, TLS fallback gating, IPv6 database functions

  -- Documentation --

[New] Man page: apf.8 covering all CLI operations, trust system, and
      configuration reference
[New] FLOW.md/FLOW: standalone order-of-operations document with INPUT chain
      precedence table and fast/full load conditions
[Change] README: modernize headers; add Quick Start; document 2.0.2 features;
      consolidate on README.md (remove plain text README); correct
      troubleshooting from 'apf -l' to 'apf --rules'
[Fix] Documentation sync: add GeoIP sections to README/man page; correct
      SYNFLOOD in FLOW, NFLOG in conf.apf, DOCKER_COMPAT values in README;
      align man page SYNOPSIS, help() options, and Key Files across all docs

  -- Test Suite --

[New] 12 new test files (22-33) and expanded coverage across existing files:
      uid-egress, devel-fastload, vnet, connlimit, hooks, temp-trust,
      synflood, block-escalation, advanced-trust, FQDN, CLI, and regression
      (612 tests across 35 files)
[New] UAT acceptance suite: 12 scenario files with 83 tests exercising
      trust lifecycle, temporary trust, firewall lifecycle, port filtering,
      advanced trust syntax, IPv6, and error paths; CI job on Debian 12
[Change] Migrate test infrastructure to batsman v1.2.0; test parallelization;
      validate_config tests use --validate saving ~55-60s; per-test teardown
      and centralized UAT cleanup to prevent cascading failures
[Fix] CI: UAT job Docker build used wrong context directory; use -f
      tests/Dockerfile with project root as build context
